      "content": "A new massive leak surfaced online, showcasing the Oppo Find X8 in real-life photos along with pretty much all the specs. The live images of the device don't reveal anything new - circular camera island on the back, extremely thin bezels on the front and flat frame design all-around. Oppo Find X8 live images The leaked spec sheet, however, gives us some missing pieces of the puzzle. The vanilla Oppo Find X8 will feature a 6.5-inch BOE-made OLED panel and will run on a still-unannounced Dimensity 9400 SoC . The camera configuration on the back will consist of three 50MP cameras - main, ultrawide and a periscope telephoto unit with 3x optical zoom. The sensor used for the telephoto shooter is Sony LYT-600. A generous 5,700 mAh battery will keep the lights on, supporting 80W fast charging and 50W magnetic wireless fast charging. What's interesting, the specs mention an alert slider and a customizable virtual pressure-sensitive button. We may see something similar to Apple's Action Button and Camera Control all in one. Additionally, the device will feature IP68 or IP69 ingress protection, while the chassis will be just 7mm thick and weigh around 190 grams. Very impressive numbers. The available colors will be Black, White, Blue and Pink. Source",
