      "content": "Tens of thousands of Kiwis were awakened by a strong, shallow earthquake centred near Wellington this morning. The magnitude 5.7 earthquake struck at a depth of 33km at 5.08am. The earthquake was centred 25km west of Wellington and was felt by 37,000 people, according to GeoNet. GeoNet said the shaking could be felt as far south as Christchurch and as far north as Auckland. An early morning shake today (6 Oct) at 5.08am in the Cook Strait with a M5.7 quake with strong shaking. It was about 33 km depth and was widely felt in the Wellington region and north of the South Island. We have received over 36,000 reports. https://t.co/95HUDjfN8S",
