      "content": "A man has been charged with the murder of a 94-year-old who was found fatally injured. West Midlands Police were called to a property off Birches Barn Road in Bradmore, in the early hours of Thursday (Oct 3) following reports of an intrusion. They found Harold Monk, who had sustained serious injuries. He died in hospital yesterday evening (Oct 4), police said. A man was arrested at the address a short time later. A man, aged 45, was charged with burglary and murder and appeared at Wolverhampton Magistrates Court. Get the latest Birmingham Live breaking news on WhatsApp He was remanded in custody and will next appear at Wolverhampton Crown Court on Monday (7 Oct). Det Insp Phil Poole, who is leading the investigation, said: \"We understand that people will be concerned, however we want to reassure everyone in the area, that we believe this was an isolated incident. \"We are not looking for anyone else in connection with this incident and our thoughts remain with Mr Monk's family who are being supported and kept updated at this most awful time.\"",
