      "description": "Swift turns 35 in December 2024 Leer",
      "content": "t's a busy couple of months for and as they celebrate their 35th birthdays together, but when exactly does the pop star sensation officially become closer to 40 than 30? First up in the celebrations book is the Kansas City Chiefs' , which he celebrates on October 5 as fans suspect will release a special music video on behalf of the three-time Super Bowl champion. Then she heads back to the Eras Tour to push across the United States and Canada before it ends for good in Vancouver on December 8, just in time for her to celebrate her own birthday a few days later on the 13th. The star was born in 1989 in West Reading, Pennsylvania, approximately 63 miles away from Philadelphia, to a stockbroker, and , who worked as a mutual fund marketing executive. is the maternal granddaughter of and recalled that heading to the opera to sing with her is one of her earliest memories and one of her most significant influences in her music journey. She and her younger brother were raised on a Christmas tree farm in their formative years, whilst they enjoyed summer home getaways to Stone Harbor in New Jersey where she refined her skills by singing in a local coffee shop. When did Taylor Swift burst onto the scene? released her debut single, Tim McGraw, from her self-titled debut album, at just 16 as the song introduced her as a fresh voice in country music, blending youthful emotion with a traditional country sound. The album went on to become a major success, especially in the country music world, and established her as a rising star but her true breakout moment came in 2008 with her second album, Fearless, particularly the hit single Love Story. The track catapulted her to global fame and the album won multiple awards and became the best-selling album of 2009 in the US, marking her transition from country star to a mainstream pop sensation.",
